}}''A Certain Scientific Railgun''({{lj|とある科学の{{ruby|超電磁砲|レールガン}}}}, a.l.a. ''Toaru Kagaku no Railgun'') is a comic series that tell a side story to the light novel ''A Certain Magical Index'' written by Kamachi Kazuma and illustrated by Motoi Fuyukawa. It's also made into TV animes. 
==The Comic==
===Basic Info===
The comic is drawn by Motoi Fuyukawa. It has been serialized in ''Gekkan Comic Dengeki Daioh'' since May 2007. 
===Background===
The story takes place in the Academy City. The Academy City is a highly developed place in terms of technology. It is said to be 20 to 30 years ahead of the rest of the world. Eighty percent of its 2.3 million residents are students. The focus of studies here is directed towards esper powers. 
===Story===
It mainly tells the story of [[Mikoto Misaka]] and things that happen around her. Misaka Mikoto, one of the top level espers in the Academy City(Level 5), shares a room with [[Kuroko Shirai]], a Level 4 esper who is a member of the Judgment. Both attend to Tokiwadai, a private school reserved for the high-leveled and the rich. Kuroko's partner at Branch 177, the Judgment, [[Kazari Uiharu]], is a Level 1<del> Level 6 Temperature Keeping Death God</del> who studies at Sakugawa middle school. Her best friend and classmate there is [[Ruiko Saten]], a Level 0{{spoiler| Level 6 Uppering Gas}}. Together the four encounter several adventures in the exciting scientific town.

==The Anime==
===1st Season===
''A Certain Scientific Railgun'' was made into TV animes in October,2009 by [[J.C.STAFF]], it has 24 episodes and an ova. 
